 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11","title":"Data, messaging, and distributed-systems parity","description":"The upstream crate also exposes database, messaging, and distributed runtime families that remain absent in ANSI C. These are not kernel details; they are concrete functional gaps visible in the exported module tree.","design":"This epic should explicitly track those gaps rather than leaving them hidden behind generic deferred-surface language.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Database, messaging, and distributed module families have explicit implementation beads with verification requirements.\\nB. Dependencies on network/service/trace/runtime layers are encoded in the graph.\\nC. Final crate-level parity cannot be declared without either implementing these or explicitly re-scoping the project.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/database/*, src/messaging/*, and src/distributed/*.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:45.102560069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:43:24.311086121Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","database","distributed","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:45.102560069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:17.847157734Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:18.940736694Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:20.044429956Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","title":"Implement database client-family parity","description":"Port the database clients that upstream exports: sqlite, postgres, mysql, pool, and transaction surfaces. Messaging clients move to a dedicated sibling task so backend-specific lifecycle, retry, and shutdown behavior can be specified cleanly.","design":"Implementation should build on the network/service/transport work with explicit resource, retry, and shutdown behavior. Include fail-closed unsupported-backend behavior where full parity is not immediately achievable.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public database module families exist or explicitly fail closed with documented limits.\\nB. Tests cover connection lifecycle, pool behavior, transaction/error semantics, and backend-specific shutdown/retry paths.\\nC. Logged integration or e2e flows exercise at least one database backend with artifact-rich diagnostics.","notes":"Keep messaging semantics in a separate bead so queueing, streaming, and broker failures get their own acceptance coverage.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T22:29:35.899979755Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","database","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:29.106794382Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.11","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:46.645751120Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:30.170290645Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.11.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:31.223249840Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}